  "informal_statement": "For every pair of real numbers a, b: min a b <= (a+b)/2 <= max a b -- the average of two numbers always lies between their minimum and maximum.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Case split on which of a, b is larger (le_total). In each case, min and max both resolve to one of a, b (min_eq_left/right, max_eq_left/right), reducing both inequalities to simple linear facts closed by linarith.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem avg_between_min_max (a b : ℝ) : min a b ≤ (a + b) / 2 ∧ (a + b) / 2 ≤ max a b",
